This is a bit complex and adds yet another way to create these proto objects to our code. If there's a bug in this approach it would be hard to catch. Why not just add a default way to create a transactionBody and record for each sub-class?
    protected abstract TransactionBody.Builder getTransactionBody();
    protected abstract TransactionRecord.Builder getTransactionRecord();
Then parent class can set any common defaults on those objects and wrap them in a RecordItem and call the generic tests in parent. For children classes, then can call getTransactionBody() and clear and set any additional fields per test case, then construct a recorditem:
getTransactionBody().getConsensusCreateTopicBuilder().clearMemo().setMemo("foo").clearAdminKey();

